QIMA is a global provider of Quality Control and Supply Chain Compliance services used by thousands of brands, retailers and importers around the world to secure, manage and optimize their global supply network. Every year, QIMA deliver some 400,000 inspections, audits, and laboratory tests all over the world. 

Our product testing Laboratory in Ho Chi Minh is specializing in consumer goods product testing. We have decades of experience in the consumer products industry: we know testing, and the regulations and standards that drive it.




OBJECTIVE 




This position is responsible to maintain a high level of quality performance in the laboratory, and ensure the testing equipment delivers the desired level of accuracy at all time. 




RESPONSIBILITIES 




1. Establish and publish local quality manual and quality system related documents to bring the laboratory’s quality systems and policies into compliance with quality systems requirement, assure the quality management systems are implemented faithfully and effectively; 

2. Handle daily quality assurance related tasks, coordinate quality related activities with team leaders; 

3. Liaise with external parties (e.g. accreditation bodies, governmental departments etc.) and responsible for accreditation, recognition and related matters. Represent company to attend any external or corporate internal audits; 

4. Approve annual internal audit plan and execute internal audit according to the plan; conduct system audits, prepare audit report, review audit findings, issue CAR and prepare audit report; 

5. Investigate customer complaint case and supervise the implementation of improvement action; 

6. Supervise equipment management, arrange external calibration to ensure the testing equipment delivers the desired level of accuracy at all times; 

7. Supervise all corrective / preventive actions ensure actions are taken timely and effective, keep related records; 

8. Arrange and host Management Review Meeting, collect input materials from all related parties, prepare management review report and submit Annual Work Report and Statistical Data according to the requirement. 

9. Other quality related tasks such as arrange proficiency testing, monitor document control system, monitor subcontractor and supplier evaluation, budget planning. 

10. Other ad hoc tasks assigned by Asia QA Manager and Head of Vietnam Laboratory.




JOB QUALIFICATION REQUIREMENTS 




EDUCATION 

Degree holder in a field related to chemistry, physics, mathematics, or engineering. 

QUALIFICATION 

Internal auditor of management system. 

TECHNICAL KNOWLEDGE 

In-depth knowledge of ISO 17025 quality management system; 
Knowledge of metrological traceability and equipment management; 
Knowledge of measurement uncertainty. 

SIKLLS 

Good planning, organizational, monitoring, communication and leadership skills; 
Good trouble shooting skills; 
Good training skills. 

EXPERIENCE 

> 2years accredited laboratory working experience with one-year experience to manage quality system as QA supervisor; 
Solid experience in handling local accreditation is a must and experience in handling foreign accreditation is an advantage; 

LANGUAGE PROFICIENCY 

Fluent in written and spoken English and Vietnamese. 

OTHERS 

Self-motivated; 
Analytical mind and logical thinking.

